 =\n|population_density_urban_km2    =\n|population_blank1_title         =\n|population_blank1               =\n|population_density_blank1_km2   =   \n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]]\n|utc_offset             = +8\n|coordinates            = {{coord|45|31|N|116|58|E|region:CN-15|display=inline,title}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = [[Postal code of China|Postal code]]\n|postal_code            = 026300\n|area_code              =\n|website                = http://www.dwq.gov.cn/\n|footnotes              =  \n}} \n'''East Ujimqin Banner''' ([[Mongolian language|Mongolian]]: {{MongolUnicode|\u1835\u1821\u182d\u1826\u1828}} {{MongolUnicode|\u1824\u1835\u1824\u182e\u1824\u1834\u1822\u1828}} {{MongolUnicode|\u182c\u1823\u1830\u1822\u182d\u1824}} ''Jeg\u00fcn Ujumu\u010din qosi\u0263u''; {{zh|s=\u4e1c\u4e4c\u73e0\u7a46\u6c81\u65d7 |t=\u6771\u70cf\u73e0\u7a46\u6c81\u65d7 |p=D\u014dng W\u016bzh\u016bm\u00f9q\u00ecn Q\u00ed}}) is a [[Banner (Inner Mongolia)|banner]] in the northeast of the [[Inner Mongolia]] Autonomous Region, People's Republic of China. It is under the administration of [[Xilin Gol League]].\n\n==Geography and climate==\n[[File:Txu-oclc-10552568-nl50-8.jpg|left|thumb|Lama H\u00fcryee S\u00fcme ({{lang|zh-hant|\u5587\u561b\u5eab\u5217\u8607\u6728}}) (1963)]]\nEast Ujimqin features a cold [[semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''BSk''), marked by long, cold and very dry winters, hot, somewhat humid summers, and strong winds, especially in spring. The monthly daily mean temperature in January, the coldest month, is {{convert|\u221220.5|\u00b0C|1}}, and in July, the warmest month, {{convert|21.4|\u00b0C|1}}, with the annual mean at {{convert|1.93|\u00b0C|1}}. The annual precipitation is approximately {{convert|251|mm|in|abbr=on}}, with more than half of it falling in July and August alone. Due to the aridity and elevation, [[diurnal temperature variation]] often exceeds {{convert|15|C-change}} in spring, averaging {{convert|13.5|C-change|1}} annually. With monthly percent possible sunshine ranging from 59% in July to 76% in February, sunshine is abundant year-round, with an annual total of 3,006 hours.\n\n{{Weather box\n|metric first=y\n|single line=y \n|location = East Ujimqin (1981\u22122010 normals)\n|Jan high C = \u221213.8\n|Feb high C =  \u22128.3\n|Mar high C =   0.7\n|Apr high C =  12.6\n|May high C =  20.3\n|Jun high C =  25.6\n|Jul high C =  27.7\n|Aug high C =  26.4\n|Sep high C =  20.2\n|Oct high C =  10.8\n|Nov high C =  \u22121.8\n|Dec high C = \u221211.1\n\n|Jan mean C = \u221220.5\n|Feb mean C = \u221216.1\n|Mar mean C =  \u22126.8\n|Apr mean C =   4.6\n|May mean C =  12.7\n|Jun mean C =  18.8\n|Jul mean C =  21.4\n|Aug mean C =  19.7\n|Sep mean C =  12.5\n|Oct mean C =   2.9\n|Nov mean C =  \u22128.8\n|Dec mean C = \u221217.2\n\n|Jan low C = \u221225.8\n|Feb low C = \u221222.3\n|Mar low C = \u221213.4\n|Apr low C =  \u22122.9\n|May low C =   4.6\n|Jun low C =  11.7\n|Jul low C =  15.4\n|Aug low C =  13.3\n|Sep low C =   5.7\n|Oct low C =  \u22123.4\n|Nov low C = \u221214.2\n|Dec low C = \u221222.1\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm =  1.8\n|Feb precipitation mm =  1.4\n|Mar precipitation mm =  4.6\n|Apr precipitation mm =  7.0\n|May precipitation mm = 17.4\n|Jun precipitation mm = 42.9\n|Jul precipitation mm = 82.4\n|Aug precipitation mm = 57.1\n|Sep precipitation mm = 20.4\n|Oct precipitation mm =  8.3\n|Nov precipitation mm =  4.6\n|Dec precipitation mm =  3.2\n\n|Jan humidity = 71\n|Feb humidity = 67\n|Mar humidity = 57\n|Apr humidity = 40\n|May humidity = 39\n|Jun humidity = 50\n|Jul humidity = 61\n|Aug humidity = 60\n|Sep humidity = 54\n|Oct humidity = 53\n|Nov humidity = 62\n|Dec humidity = 70\n|unit precipitation days = 0.1 mm\n|Jan precipitation days =  3.6\n|Feb precipitation days =  3.4\n|Mar precipitation days =  3.8\n|Apr precipit